cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with optical flow estimation, which is a classic problem in computer vision. The use of deep learning and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The extension of DenseNet to a fully convolutional network for unsupervised learning could also make it relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method on standard benchmarks could make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
